when setting up the settings, would drag and drop clipboard from my pc to the VM only, would that be fine or still dangerous5:35 PMWeighed unidirectional clipboard sharing security implicationsWeighed unidirectional clipboard sharing security implicationsGood question — these are two separate features with different risk profiles.

Clipboard (Bidirectional)
Fine to enable. Text copied from your host to the VM (or vice versa) is just text. Claude cannot trigger a clipboard read unprompted — it can only use what you paste into the chat window manually.
The one real risk: if you copy a password or API key on your host and then switch to the VM without clearing the clipboard, Claude could potentially read it if a tool calls for clipboard access. Easy mitigation: clear your clipboard before switching contexts (Win + V → Clear All on Windows).
Set it to Host to Guest only if you want to be strict — that way you can paste into the VM but nothing from the VM can reach your Windows clipboard automatically.

Drag and Drop
More caution warranted. Dragging files from your Windows PC into the VM is functionally the same as copying to the shared folder — low risk for that direction. But Guest to Host drag-and-drop means files generated inside the VM (potentially by Claude) could land anywhere on your real Windows desktop without going through your controlled C:\ClaudeProjects folder.

Recommended settings
In VirtualBox → Settings → General → Advanced:
FeatureSettingReasonClipboardHost to GuestYou can paste into VM; VM can't push to your real clipboardDrag and DropHost to GuestYou can drag files in; Claude can't drag files out to your real PC
This keeps the shared folder as the only exit path for anything Claude produces — which is exactly what the security setup was designed for.
